       <h2>Who is developing Salsa?</h2>

      <p>Salsa is an open-source web application being developed at <a href="http://usu.edu/">Utah State University</a>. The Salsa project team is located at the <a href="http://cidi.usu.edu/">Center for Innovative Design &amp; Instruction</a>. The Salsa project has received funding from the <a href="http://ustar.usu.edu/">Utah Science and Technology Research</a> intiative.<p>
      <p>A small number of higher-education institutions have been accepted into a pilot program. Candidates are still being considered. Please contact the project at <a href="mailto:salsa@usu.edu">salsa@usu.edu.</a>
    </div><!-- /.col-sm-6 -->
    <div class="col-sm-12">
      <h2>How does Salsa work?</h2>
      <p>Salsa generates a unique and random hyperlink for you. Bookmark or copy your hyperlink with the "My SALSA" button. Use the hyperlink to return and edit your SALSAs. Publish your SALSAs to generate a new hyperlink to a "read-only" copy of your Salsa in HTML format. No email address or signup is required.</p>
